  "text": "The objective of this paper is a game theoretic exploration of an alternative market mechanism for the control reserves with potential improvements. To further discuss this, we briefly discuss relevant features of the existing market mechanism. Control reserves are categorized as primary, secondary, and tertiary. Primary reserves balance frequency deviations in timescale of seconds. Secondary reserves balance the deviations on a timescale of seconds to minutes not resolved by primary control. Tertiary reserves restore secondary reserves and typically act 15 minutes after a disturbance to frequency. The secondary and tertiary control reserves in several countries are procured in a market. In the Swiss market for example, the auction mechanism implemented by the Transmission System Operator (TSO) minimizes the cost of procurement of required amounts of power, given bids [CITATION_1] ).",
